sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>(Kuadrant)
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Limitador as Limitador<br/>(Kuadrant)
    participant PayloadProc as payload-processing<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant KServe as KServe Model Endpoint<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ExtLLM as External LLM Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP TLS

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Client,ExtLLM: Flow 1: Model Inference (API Key Authentication)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /{namespace}/{model}:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-* API key
        Gateway->>Authorino: Auth evaluation<br/>(API key credential)
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>NetworkPolicy-restricted
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Lookup key hash<br/>(SHA-256 with per-key salt)
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key record + subscription binding
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Validation result + identity
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>NetworkPolicy-restricted
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Selected subscription + limits
        Authorino->>Limitador: Token rate limit check<br/>(gRPC, mTLS)
        Limitador-->>Authorino: Allow/Deny
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth result<br/>(strip Authorization header)
        Gateway->>PayloadProc: ext_proc request<br/>gRPC/9004, TLS SIMPLE
        PayloadProc-->>Gateway: Model name extraction<br/>API translation<br/>Credential injection
        alt KServe Model
            Gateway->>KServe: Forward inference<br/>HTTPS/443, injected credential
            KServe-->>Gateway: Prediction response
        else External Model
            Gateway->>ExtLLM: Forward inference<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS SIMPLE<br/>Injected backend API key
            ExtLLM-->>Gateway: Prediction response
        end
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 2: API Key Creation (User Token Auth)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer OpenShift token
        Gateway->>Authorino: Auth evaluation<br/>(OpenShift token)
        Authorino->>Gateway: KubernetesTokenReview<br/>HTTPS/443
        Note right of Authorino: Validates token via<br/>K8s TokenReview API
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Identity (X-MaaS-Username,<br/>X-MaaS-Group headers)
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS 1.2+
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Store key hash<br/>(SHA-256, per-key salt,<br/>show-once pattern)
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key stored
        MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: API key (plaintext, shown once)
        Gateway-->>Client: API key response
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client,KServe: Flow 3: Model Listing with Access Probing
        Client->>Gateway: GET /v1/models<br/>Auth: Bearer token / API key
        Gateway->>Authorino: Auth evaluation
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Identity headers
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: GET /v1/models<br/>HTTPS/8443
        loop Per model (concurrent, max 10)
            MaaSAPI->>KServe: GET /v1/models<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer passthrough<br/>(InsecureSkipVerify for cluster-internal)
            KServe-->>MaaSAPI: Model info or 403
        end
        MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: Accessible models list
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON model list
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
        Note over Gateway,ExtLLM: Flow 4: ExternalModel Reconciliation (Controller)
        Note over Gateway: maas-controller watches<br/>ExternalModel CRs
        Gateway->>Gateway: Create ExternalName Service<br/>+ ServiceEntry (MESH_EXTERNAL)<br/>+ DestinationRule (TLS SIMPLE)<br/>+ HTTPRoute (path + header match)
        Note over Gateway,ExtLLM: At inference time, Gateway routes<br/>to external provider via Istio networking
    end
